x4freetext: Details of
experimental method, including polarimeter calibration.
The polarization data were obtained by using
the 33 MeV polarized He-3 beam. The average
polarization was 33% and the on-target intensity
averaged 0.5 nA. The polarimeter used to monitor the
beam polarization from 33 to 18 MeV was based on the
elastic  scattering of He-3 by H-2.
six silicon surface barrier
detector telescopes. The delta-E detectors were of
thickness in range 50 to 80 mum and the E-detectors
were 0.9 mm thick.

x4codes.hlp: Univ. of Birmingham, England, United Kingdom

x4freetext: A.V.F. cyclotron.
The target was  a He-3 gas cell operated at 1.8-2.0 bar
absolute pressure. The beam exit and entrance windows
were made of 6.4 mum Havar, although 12.5 mum Melinex
has been successfully used for some measurements.
The target thickness varied from 0.19 mg/cm**2 at 12-
degree to 0.14 mg/cm**2 at 45 degree
*By authors*.The measurements at energies lower than
the main beam energy were obtained by using aluminiun
energy degraders placed before the beam entrance
window of the target cell.
*By compiler*.The cross section angular distributions
He-3(He-3,el), which were reported by authors in paper,
are taken from reference-J,PR/C,5,1622,1970 and
J,PR/C,9,149,1974- author`s comment, but compiler not
found such  cross section in indicated papers.
.Phase shift analysis.
.The average uncertainty in the target thickness
as seen by the detectors produced an uncertainty in the
energy loss which has been calculated to be 0.01 MeV.
The statistical uncertainties are given by
the authors only.
